\item{}When \(x = 10\), graph the point \(50 + 5x\)%
\item{}When \(x\gt 10\), graph the line \(90 + 6x\)%
\end{itemize}
Mathematically, this is often abbreviated as%
\begin{equation*}
\begin{cases}
50 + 5x & \text{ if } x\lt 10 \\ 
125     & \text{ if } x = 10 \\ 
90 + 6x & \text{ if } x\gt 10 \\ 
\end{cases}
\end{equation*}
