\amp = \frac{1}{5}5x^4 - 4x^3\\
\amp = x^4 - 4x^3
\end{align*}
\(f'=0\) if and only if%
\begin{align*}
x^4-4x^3 \amp =0\\
x^3(x-4) \amp =0
\end{align*}
\(f'=0\) if \(x=0\) or \(x=4\).%
\par
\(f'\) is a polynomial so there are no values where \(f'\ DNE\). \begin{image}{0.25}{0.5}{0.25}{}%
